name: Line Plot
text: The line plot shows the value of a selected feature for each data point.

name: Histograms
text: In statistics, a histogram is representation of the distribution of numerical data, where the data are binned and the count for each bin is represented.

name: Aggregations
text: Aggregates are a type of transform that can be applied to values in a given expression.

name: Probability Density Functions and Cumulative Distribution Function
text: The PDF returns the expected probability for observing a value.  The CDF returns the expected probability for observing a value less than or equal to a given value.

name: box plot
text: A box plot is a statistical representation of numerical data through their quartiles. The ends of the box represent the lower and upper quartiles, while the median (second quartile) is marked by a line inside the box.

name: Violin Plot
text: A violin plot is a statistical representation of numerical data. It is similar to a box plot, with the addition of a rotated kernel density plot on each side.
